history.content:
The fall '20 website just hasn't been set up/made public yet. That note was probably just put there automatically or a bit early.

Meanwhile, if you want to learn more about the class content, try looking at the website from Professor Dragan's offering last fall.

Of course, if you're specifically interested in logistics and such related to the online format in the fall, you'll just have to wait, or try to contact an instructor.

On classes.berkeley.edu, cs188 has a note that said:

"To learn more, visit the class webpage: https://inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/~cs188/fa20/"

But when I tried to follow the link, I'm getting a "permission denied" error. Anyone else having this issue?
history.subject: Can't access cs188 course info for fall 20?
